net.sourceforge.waters.model.base

Class IndexedArrayList<P extends NamedProxy>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<P>
        • net.sourceforge.waters.model.base.IndexedArrayList<P>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<P>, Collection<P>, List<P>, IndexedCollection<P>, IndexedList<P>

    public class IndexedArrayList<P extends NamedProxy>
extends AbstractList<P>
implements IndexedList<P>, Cloneable, Serializable
    An array list implementation of the IndexedCollection interface.

    This implementation is based an ArrayList backed by a HashMap to map names to the elements of the list. It therefore provides fast access to elements given their name, while maintaining their order. All elements added to a IndexedArrayList must be of type NamedProxy.

    Author:
    Robi Malik

      • reinsert

        public void reinsert(NamedProxy proxy,
                     String newname)
        Description copied from interface: IndexedCollection

        Reinserts an item into this collection to see whether its name can be changed. This method removes the given item from this collection and inserts it under the given new name. The name of the item must be unchanged prior to this call.

        This method is intended to be called prior to changing the name of an item in a setName() method. An exception will be thrown if the item cannot be renamed in this collection. If this method returns successfully, the caller should change the item's name to restore consistency.

        Specified by:
        reinsert in interface IndexedCollection<P extends NamedProxy>
        Parameters:
        proxy - The item to be renamed.
        newname - The new name for the item.
